    "what_description": "Nordenstamia stellatopilosa is a species of flowering plant in the family Asteraceae. It is a shrub with a woody base, growing up to 1 meter in height, and has a taproot system. The leaves are linear, 5-15 cm long, and have a glabrous surface with a serrated margin. The plant produces capitula, consisting of 12-15 white florets and 3-4 yellow disc florets, which are surrounded by a ring of phyllaries. The plant is native to the high-altitude regions of the Andes in South America, where it grows in rocky and stony areas.",
